Diagnosis.
A large and robust species (body length: 
16.5–20.7 mm
) with greatly elongate, anterolaterally directed and apically usually recurved humeral processes (
Figs 80–83
). The diagnostic male terminalia (
Fig. 15
), paramere (
Figs 40–41
) and female terminalia (
Fig. 54
) are illustrated in the present paper.
